Quick Start Guide
Clone the repository:
git clone https://github.com/your-org/oncoai.git
cd oncoai

Set up environment:
cp .env.example .env
# Edit .env with your AWS configuration

Deploy:
chmod +x deploy.sh
./deploy.sh

Access the application:

Frontend: http://your-amplify-app.com

API: https://your-api-gateway-url.amazonaws.com/prod

Run a test campaign:
python3 test_oncoai.py https://your-api-gateway-url.amazonaws.com/prod

Key Features Implemented
вњ… Fully Serverless Architecture - All AWS services are serverless

вњ… Periodic Memory System - OpenSearch vector database for learning from failures

вњ… Generative Chemistry - CVAE for novel molecule generation

вњ… Multi-objective Optimization - Binding, toxicity, and drug-likeness

вњ… Computational Validation - AutoDock Vina integration

вњ… Real-time Dashboard - React.js with 3D visualization

вњ… One-click Deployment - AWS CDK infrastructure as code

вњ… Comprehensive Testing - Integration tests included

